==> The include directory for iconv is: /usr/gnu/include
==> The runtime link flag for iconv is: -L/usr/gnu/lib -liconv

and do the following, replacing what is below with the correct values if they differ:

# export CFLAGS=-I/usr/gnu/include
# export PERL_MM_OPT="$PERL_MM_OPT LDDLFLAGS=\"`perl -MConfig -e 'print $Config{lddlflags} . shift' \" -Wl,-R/usr/gnu/lib -L/usr/gnu/lib -liconv\"`\""
# echo "CFLAGS is: $CFLAGS"
# echo "PERL_MM_OPT is: $PERL_MM_OPT"
# perl Makefile.PL
# make
# make test
# make install

We have set CFLAGS environment variable and LDDLFLAGS in PERL_MM_OPT for the following reasons:
- objects that depend on iconv are built using ExtUtils::CBuilder <=> CFLAGS environment variable is appended to compile flags
- final ESLIF.so is built using ExtUtils::MakeMaker <=> PERL_MM_OPT environment variable to set link and runtime informations

